content: WOOOW! Kyle, big PP! I very rarely find myself as captivated by mobile game, as I found myself playing Immortal Rogue. Full 12 hours day went down the drain since the moment I installed it! It feels a bit repetitive at times but does it really matter if I still wasn't able to put my phone down? Nah! Saw some people complaining about not-so-good controls (which are gesture-based) but I bet it's because they didn't spend enough time to get used to it. I had no such problem! BUY!

Great rogue-lite game! Progression during and between runs is well designed. Controls are simple and feel strong. The story is fun, allowing you to make choices that alter the course of a society in a cyclical progression of civilization. A few negatives: Sometimes your character will get stuck on the scenery, which can prove fatal. You also unlock everything a bit too quickly. Also, the thralls that are supposed to give you a revive don't seem to work. Still, one of my top fav mobile games!

content: Very fun, very fast and every run is different from each other, so you wont get bored in a while. But I find it still lacks a little bit of content, I really hope they add more stuff on future updates, even if they come as small dlc

This is a very fun, unique, and challenging game. There are only a few flaws, but it just released and I have confidence in the dev. Sometimes you become stuck in the wall; easy to fix. I had a "FATAL ERROR" pop-up that closed during a long run. games can get that for something as simple as a ';' out of place. If that's true: easy fix. My biggest issue (still a small one) is the lack of landscape mode. The phone is awkward to hold vertical while gaming. No need to tweak controls... just rotate.

Combat system is entertaining. However, I've had two major problems with clipping. One time, my character got stuck on a tree and could not move. Another time, the last enemy was stuck in an unaccessible part of the map. The lack of a reset is ridiculous. Still fun, but very flawed bugs that require reinstalling after much progress limits my ability to recommend it.

I had to refund it because the controls got to me too much, the constant swiping and tapping the screen and hoping I'd hit an enemy were getting to me too much. I'll keep an eye on this game though and may visit it in the future after a few updates. Dev, I want your game to succeed, it looks awesome & has a ton of potential for greatness! The only recommendation I have is to consider adding virtual and physical gamepad controls, and maybe include a tutorial for controls in game. Still, good job!

Fun game despite terrible controls. Not going to lie, they're so bad I considered getting a refund. It's quick and repetitive with unlockables to work toward. Each level you get a to choose between two choices of targets. The target you hunt determines how the world progresses (and what the next level is). Neat game, bad controls.
My new favorite game. It keeps pulling me in for one more run.

A very well designed roguelike that follows a vampire whose choices while feeding determine the course of human civilisation as it waxes and wanes from galactic superpower to warring tribes and back. The gameplay is similar to Nuclear Throne and the persistent upgrades are like those in Dead Cells. The weapons are diverse and punchy and the controls are spot-on. However there are some collision bugs, especially with the environmental hazards. Kindly fix those. Otherwise the game is fantastic.

Don't let the price scare anyone, especially as it's cheap enough to try. Stumbled across this Rogue-lite and I love it. Caught a little off guard initially by the run didn't reset on death, but continues endlessly for new paths as you upgrade. This is not a Twin Stick shooter, but rather operates by Dashes(Swipes) to move around, Taps for regular attacks, and Tap'n'Hold to Aim and use Heavy(Special) Attacks. Various weapons give different styles, so it's not repetitive.
